  "text": "held by men were, on average, 1.6 times more powerful than those held by women. These findings reflect the gendered allocation of cabinet portfolios elsewhere (Franceschet and Thomas, 2012; [CITATION_1] . The new women ministers included several women still in their 30s, alongside some more senior women such as Lebranchu. Given that only four members of the entire government (including the president, prime minister and all other men) had previous ministerial experience, the relatively junior status of some of the new women in government should not be a significant disadvantage.",
